Smart Home Automation System Report

This document outlines the design and implementation of a Bluetooth-based smart home automation system using Arduino and Android. The system allows control of multiple home appliances wirelessly via a mobile phone.

Components:
- Arduino Uno/Nano
- Bluetooth module HC-05
- Relay modules
- Android phone with control app

Functionality:
- The Android app sends commands to Arduino.
- Arduino receives the Bluetooth signal and activates the appropriate relay.
- Appliances are turned on or off accordingly.

Applications:
- Home automation
- Remote switching
- Energy saving solutions

Future Work:
- Add voice control
- Add Wi-Fi and mobile app support
